# Phase 35.6 · Final Report and Release Handoff

Repository: `cvsz/zdash`

Execution profile: DeepSeek V4 Flash Free / fast free coding model.

Goal:
Produce the final Phase 35 release-candidate report and handoff after Phase 35.1–35.5 validation. Do not make code changes unless a critical, small, obvious validation blocker is discovered.

---

## Safety invariants

- Do not enable live trading.
- Do not add broker execution.
- Do not bypass Guardian, TradingService, ExecutionEngine, SignalValidationService, RBAC, audit/event logging, dry-run mode, or safety policy.
- AI Trader remains simulation-only.
- Billing provider remains mock by default.
- Stripe remains disabled by default.
- Marketplace plugin runtime remains sandboxed by default.
- Enterprise export remains safe by default and requires confirmation for secrets.
- Do not commit secrets or local-only artifacts.
- Backend port is `8005`.

---

## Inspect first

Inspect final state:

```text
git status --short
git log --oneline -20
README.md
Makefile
.env.example
frontend/.env.example
docs/
docs/prompts/
docs/AI_TRADER_CONTROL_PLANE.md
backend/app/main.py
backend/app/ai_trader/
backend/app/api/ai_trader.py
frontend/src/api/aiTrader.ts
frontend/src/components/trading/AITraderSimulationCard.tsx
.github/workflows/
.codex/cloud/maintenance.sh
```

Do not inspect massive directories unnecessarily. Focus on release evidence.

---

## Final validation commands

Run or cite the most recent successful run. If no recent run exists, run:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
make safety-scan
```

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate-fast
```

If Docker is available and time permits:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate
```

If Docker is unavailable or too slow, report Docker validation as skipped with reason.

